; ==============================================================================
; ContentCapture Pro - Sample Captures
; ==============================================================================
; These are example captures to help you get started.
; Feel free to delete them once you've created your own!
;
; To use: Type ::welcome:: or ::ahkdocs:: anywhere
; ==============================================================================

[welcome]
url=https://github.com/yourusername/ContentCapture-Pro
title=Welcome to ContentCapture Pro!
date=2025-12-16 12:00:00
tags=tutorial,reference
note=Your first capture - delete this when ready!
opinion=This is where you'd add your personal thoughts about the content.
body=<<<BODY
🎉 Congratulations! ContentCapture Pro is working!

Try these commands:
• Type ::welcome:: anywhere to paste this content
• Type ::welcome?:: to see all options
• Type ::welcomego:: to open the URL
• Press Ctrl+Alt+B to browse all captures
• Press Ctrl+Alt+Space for quick search

Now go capture your first webpage with Ctrl+Alt+P!
BODY>>>

[ahkdocs]
url=https://www.autohotkey.com/docs/v2/
title=AutoHotkey v2 Documentation
date=2025-12-16 12:00:00
tags=reference,tutorial,programming
note=Official AHK v2 documentation
opinion=Essential reference for AutoHotkey scripting
body=<<<BODY
AutoHotkey v2 is a powerful scripting language for Windows automation.

Key resources:
• Documentation: https://www.autohotkey.com/docs/v2/
• Forums: https://www.autohotkey.com/boards/
• Tutorial: https://www.autohotkey.com/docs/v2/Tutorial.htm

ContentCapture Pro is built entirely with AHK v2!
BODY>>>

[sample]
url=https://example.com/sample-article
title=Sample Article for Testing
date=2025-12-16 12:00:00
tags=tutorial
note=This is just a sample to show the capture format
opinion=Delete this and create your own captures!
short=Check out this sample article! https://example.com/sample-article
body=<<<BODY
This is a sample capture demonstrating the body content area.

You can store:
• Full article text
• Recipe instructions  
• Code snippets
• Notes and research
• Anything you want to recall later!

The "short" field above contains a pre-made short version for social media.
When you paste on Bluesky or Twitter, it will use this shorter text automatically.
BODY>>>
